ect the <em>printer-friendly version</em> link visible at the bottom of a book page\'s content to generate a printer-friendly display of the page and all of its subsections.','','none'),(3029,'','default','The book module offers a means to organize a collection of related content pages, collectively known as a book. When viewed, this content automatically displays links to adjacent book pages, providing a simple navigation system for creating and reviewing structured content.','','none'),(3030,'','default','The outline feature allows you to include pages in the <a href=\"@book\">Book hierarchy</a>, as well as move them within the hierarchy or to <a href=\"@book-admin\">reorder an entire book</a>.','','none'),(3031,'','default','Create new books','','none'),(3032,'','default','Add content and child pages to books','','none'),(3033,'','default','View printer-friendly books','','none'),(3034,'','default','View a book page and all of its sub-pages as a single document for ease of printing. Can be performance heavy.','','none'),(3035,'','default','<em>Books</em> have a built-in hierarchical navigation. Use for handbooks or tutorials.','','none'),(3036,'','default','Allows users to create and organize related content in an outline.','','7.28'),(3037,'','default','The Color module allows users with the <em>Administer site configuration</em> permission to quickly and easily change the color scheme of themes that have been built to be compatible with it. For more information, see the online handbook entry for <a href=\"@color\">Color module</a>.','','7.28'),(3038,'','default','Changing colors','','7.28'),(3039,'','default','Using the Color module allows you to easily change the color of links, backgrounds, text, and other theme elements. To change the color settings for a compatible theme, select the <em>Settings</em> link for your theme on the <a href=\'@configure\'>Themes administration page</a>. If you don\'t see a color picker on that page, then your theme is not compati